# NSD Data Directory

This directory contains the Natural Scenes Dataset (NSD) data files required for training and inference.

## Required Files

### fMRI Data
NSD fMRI inputs are in **fsaverage** surface space, using the **`betas_fithrf_GLMdenoise_RR`**  preprocessing.

`fmri_v2.npz` - Main fMRI recordings from NSD subjects:
- Voxels are selected according to algonauts mask
- Each session is z-scored and repeats are averaged for each image
- `single_sub_fmri` - fMRI data for images only a single subject saw
- `single_sub` - corresponding subject id for single_sub_fmri
- `multi_sub_fmri` - fMRI measurements for images all subjects saw (voxels concatenated across subjects)
- `type_sample` - for each of the 73K images: 1 = single subject saw, 2 = all subjects saw, 0 = none saw

`num_voxels_all_subjects.npy` - Number of voxels per subject

### Image Data
all_images is an image array of 73K images from the NSD experiment where each index corresponds to NSD_id

ext_images is an image array from https://cocodataset.org/#download 2017 Unlabeled images

## Data Source

The NSD dataset should be downloaded from the official Natural Scenes Dataset website:
https://naturalscenesdataset.org/
